{
  "uid": "{{ alert_uid }}",
  "title": "Disk IO Wait Time Alert",
  "folderUID": "{{ folder_uid }}",
  "ruleGroup": "{{ rulegroup }}",
  "condition": "C",
  "data": [
    {
      "refId": "A",
      "relativeTimeRange": {
        "from": 900,
        "to": 0
      },
      "datasourceUid": "{{ datasourceUid }}",
      "model": {
        "refId": "A",
        "query": "SELECT last(\"io_await\") AS \"IO Wait\" FROM \"diskio\" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY time(5m), project, zone, host, \"name\" fill(0)",
        "rawQuery": true
      }
    },
    {
      "refId": "B",
      "relativeTimeRange": {
        "from": 0,
        "to": 0
      },
      "datasourceUid": "__expr__",
      "model": {
        "type": "reduce",
        "expression": "A",
        "reducer": "last"
      }
    },
    {
      "refId": "C",
      "relativeTimeRange": {
        "from": 0,
        "to": 0
      },
      "datasourceUid": "__expr__",
      "model": {
        "type": "threshold",
        "expression": "B",
        "conditions": [
          {
            "evaluator": {
              "type": "gt",
              "params": [100]
            },
            "operator": {
              "type": "and"
            },
            "query": {
              "params": ["C"]
            },
            "reducer": {
              "type": "last",
              "params": []
            },
            "type": "query"
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "interval": "1m",
  "for": "5m",
  "noDataState": "OK",
  "execErrState": "Error",
  "labels": {
    "platform": "{{ project }}",
    "zone": "{{ zone }}",
    "severity": "CRITICAL",
        "type": "{{ (rulegroup | string).split('_')[0] }}"
  },
  "annotations": {
    "summary": "Disk IO wait time is high (>50ms).",
    "description": "üßê **Why This Happens**\n- High disk IO wait indicates potential bottlenecks in storage subsystem.\n- Could be caused by heavy disk operations, slow storage, or overloaded I/O.\n\nüîç **Impact**\n- Applications may experience latency or timeout.\n- Database and file operations could slow down.\n- Overall system performance may degrade.\n\n‚úÖ **Immediate Actions for Ops**\n1. **Check current disk IO:**\n   ```\n   iostat -x 1 10\n   ```\n2. **Identify processes causing high IO:**\n   ```\n   pidstat -d 1 10\n   iotop -o\n   ```\n3. **Check disk usage and health:**\n   ```\n   df -h\n   smartctl -a /dev/sdX\n   ```\n4. **If persistent high IO:**\n   - Investigate application load.\n   - Consider moving heavy workloads to other disks.\n   - Check storage subsystem for errors or saturation.\n5. Document the issue and notify relevant teams for remediation.\n\n‚ö† **Note:** This alert triggers if `io_await` exceeds **50ms** continuously for **5 minutes**, indicating a possible disk performance bottleneck."
  },
  "isPaused": false
}


